<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id5b5b6358-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c" identifier="/us/usc/t29/s1856"><num value="1856">§ 1856.</num><heading> Waiver of rights</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Agreements by employees purporting to waive or to modify their rights under this chapter shall be void as contrary to public policy, except that a waiver or modification of rights in favor of the Secretary shall be valid for purposes of enforcement of this chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id5b5b6359-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c">(<ref href="/us/pl/97/470/tV/s506">Pub. L. 97–470, title V, § 506</ref>, <date date="1983-01-14">Jan. 14, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/96/2598">96 Stat. 2598</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id5b5b635a-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id5b5b635b-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="id5b5b635c-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective 90 days from <date date="1983-01-14">Jan. 14, 1983</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/97/470/s524">section 524 of Pub. L. 97–470</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t29/s1801">section 1801 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
